translated:
Lars Georg, provincial physician, Jörlanda, b. 2/8/98 in Kärrbo, Västmanland. Son of Governor Claes W. and Charlotte Levénhaupt. Married on 26th May to Ulla Cederström. Children: Birgitta born in 1927, Sten born in 1920, Anne-Marie born in 1930, Ulrika born in 1931, Margareta born in 1934, Cecilia born in 1940, Elisabeth born in 1942, Claes-Johan born in 1944. Education: Västerås matriculation exam in 1916, medical candidate at Uppsala University in 1922, medical license from Karolinska Institute in 1927. Assistant doctor at Nyköping hospital in 1924, acting provincial physician in Bjurholm district for short periods in 1926 and 1927, assistant doctor and acting deputy head physician at Karlshamn hospital for thirteen months in 1926-1927, acting provincial physician in Fräntorps and Svenljunga districts for short periods in 1927 and 1928, employed by Tranemo municipality in 1927-1928, acting deputy provincial physician in Tranemo district in 1929-1930, appointed as regular deputy provincial physician in 1930, provincial physician in Jörlanda district since 1942, railway physician for Falkenberg railways in 1928-1934. Chairman of the Tranemo health council from 1930 to 1934, chairman of the Jörlanda district of the Swedish Red Cross since 1943.

Claes Evald Wesberg, rector, Trollhättan, b. 30/5/91 in Torslanda, Gothenburg and Bohuslän. Son of Edvard W. and Charlotta Tönnesdotter. First married in 1921 to Gertrud Lindqvist, deceased in 1927; second married in 1931 to Ruth Lindqvist. Children: Claès-Henrik born in 1922, Gertrud born in 1926. Education: Graduated from Gothenburg higher Latin school in 1911, Bachelor of Arts from Gothenburg University in 1915, Master of Arts in 1916, teacher at Norra latin school in Stockholm in the spring term of 1928. Temporary subject teacher in Vara municipality between school years 1916 and 1917, substitute subject teacher in Nässjö during 1917-1918, teacher at Trollhättan private school in 1918-1919, subject teacher at Trollhättan municipal middle school in 1919-1927, adjunct in mother tongue, German and history with social studies at Trollhättan secondary school since 1928, acting rector from 1920-1921, rector of the municipal middle school from 1921-1930, rector of the secondary school since 1930. Auditor for church accounts and administration from 1929-1931, advocate for freedom of the press from 1931, representative for oversight of a certain school fund, inspector for vocational schools, member of the church council. Traveled to Germany in 1912, 1921, and 1937, participated in Swedish Red Cross invalid transport in 1915 and 1917. Awarded with RVO (Order of Vasa), RLSF (Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences), and silver medal.

Thérèse, dentist, Gothenburg, born in Malmtö, daughter of railway engineer and shipbuilder A. P. Wessberg and Kerstin Andreasson. Graduated from Amelie Flygt School in Stockholm in 1911, dentist candidate in 1902, became a dentist in 1904. Assistant dentist in Hässleholm in 1904, practice in Västervik from 1905-1912, assistant dentist in Falkenberg from 1912-1915, school dentist in Gothenburg from 1916-1942, started her own practice in Gothenburg in 1924.

Claes Hugo Wessén, major, Halmstad, b. 26/11/96 in Veinge, Halland. Son of editor Viktor Larsson and Sigrid Wessén. Married in 1921 to Margit Drakenberg. Children: Barbro born in 1923, Birgitta born in 1929, Gunvor born in 1934. Education: Halmstad matriculation exam in 1915, officer exam in 1917, signal course in 1924 and 1929. Ensign in Västgöta Regiment in 1917, lieutenant in 1919, in Halland Regiment in 1928, captain in 1932, major in the army since 1945. Mobilization officer from 1940. Secretary in Halland First Cavalry Association from 1933-1937, chief instructor from 1938-1940, member of the executive committee from 1935-1945. Awarded with RSO (Sword of Honor), CFBGM (Royal Halland Infantry Regiment's Gold Medal), Halland County Association's Gold Medal.

Daniel Gotthold Johannes Wessén, lawyer, Mjölby, b. 27/10/96 in Högby, Östergötland. Son of Pastor C. G. Wessén and Lydia Sehman. Education: Linköping matriculation exam in 1914, law degree from Uppsala University in 1919, court clerk in Lysings, Göstrings, and Mjölby districts from 1921-1924. Established own law practice in Mjölby in 1924. Member of the Swedish Bar Association since 1936. Authorized to manage the Mjölby Canonry Estate from 1941. Member of the city council. Has written several papers on legal subjects.
